const char* const Arr_Bezier_curve_traits_2_Point_2___class__ = "The Point_2 class nested within the B zier traits class is used to represent: (i) an endpoint of a B zier curve, (ii) a vertical tangency point of a curve, used to subdivide it into $x$ -monotone subcurve, and (iii) an intersection point between two curves. While, points of type (i) have rational coordinates and are given as part of the input, points of the two latter types have algebraic coordinates. However, to speed up the arrangement construction, such point are not computed in an exact manner, and instead are given in an approximate representation. Note that the exact coordinates of a point may only be accessed if it is exactly computed. In addition to the methods listed below, the copy constructor and assignment operator for Point_2 objects are also supported.";
