const char* const Arr_polycurve_traits_2_Curve_2___class__ = "The Curve_2 type nested in the Arr_polycurve_traits_2 represents general continuous piecewise-linear subcurves (a polycurve can be self-intersecting) and support their construction from range of subcurves. Construction of polycurves in various ways is supported using the construction functors. It is strongly recommended to avoid construction of Curve_2 objects directly and prefer the usage of the construction functors. The type Curve_2 has two template parameters, namely SubcurveType_2 and PointType_2 , which are SubcurveTraits_2::Curve_2 and SubcurveTraits_2::Point_2 types. Thus, in general, the subcurves that a Curve_2 instance comprises could be either $x$ -monotone or not! The copy and default constructor as well as the assignment operator are provided for polycurve subcurves. In addition, an operator<< for the subcurves is defined for standard output streams, and an operator>> for the subcurves is defined for standard input streams.";
